## Visual Design Checklist

### Typography
- [ ] Maximum two typefaces used
- [ ] Body text minimum 16px
- [ ] Consistent heading hierarchy
- [ ] No all-caps body text
- [ ] Line length 50–75 characters for body text

### Color
- [ ] WCAG AA contrast ratios met
- [ ] Color not used as sole indicator of meaning
- [ ] Maximum 3–4 colors in palette
- [ ] Accent color used consistently
- [ ] Palette reviewed with color blindness simulator

### Layout
- [ ] Grid or alignment system applied
- [ ] Sufficient white space throughout
- [ ] No screen contains more than 
      75 words of body text
- [ ] Consistent margins applied
- [ ] Visual hierarchy clear on every screen

### Imagery
- [ ] All images serve an instructional purpose
- [ ] Image style consistent throughout
- [ ] Images are high resolution
- [ ] Diverse, representative imagery used
- [ ] Decorative images marked as decorative

### Consistency
- [ ] Navigation elements in same 
      position throughout
- [ ] Consistent visual treatment 
