## Common Visual Design Mistakes

- **Death by bullet point** — walls of text 
  with no visual support
- **Clipart and stock photo mixing** — 
  inconsistent image styles on the same screen
- **Too many fonts** — more than two 
  typefaces creates visual noise
- **Low contrast** — text that requires 
  effort to read
- **Centered everything** — overuse of 
  center alignment for body content
- **Decorative animation** — movement 
  that adds extraneous load
- **Ignoring the grid** — elements placed 
  arbitrarily rather than aligned
- **Color overload** — too many colors 
  with no hierarchy or system
- **Generic stock photos** — images that 
  signal "this is a compliance course" 
  before a word is read
- **Crowded screens** — filling every 
  pixel instead of letting content breathe

